orders from chief artisans and checks if root cause analysis done correctly, materials allocations correct, materials availability in stores & whether the hospital still has a budget allocation). Authorises the dispatch of materials from the stores. Monitors and reports on the performance of chief artisans & artisans and escalates disciplinary issues to regional head or resident engineer. Identifies the need for training for specific artisans. Attend planner\u2019s maintenance forums and meetings. Initiates a purchase requisition in SAP to call-out framework contractors. Processes time claims, call-out claims are signed off by chief artisans/inspectors and updates on the computerised maintenance management system. Collects and submit contractor performance history to the framework contracts manager. Compiles daily reports on backlogs & non-performance and report to regional head and maintenance hub. Compiles a weekly technical and budget/expenditure report for the FMU/CEO of facilities. Compiles a monthly report on productive/ unproductive hours for artisans/chief artisans. Operates the CMMS. Validates that CMMS is fully operational for the DID staff & Client. Reports all CMMS performance defects to ICT. Report periodically to the regional head on maintenance performance of the regional hubs and maintenance personnel. Notes PLEASE NOTE: To apply for the above position, please apply online at http://professionaljobcentre.gpg.gov.za Only online applications will be considered and for general enquiries please contact Human Resource on 060 983 2677. NB:. It is our intention to promote representivity (race, gender and disability) in the Public Service through the filling of this post and candidates whose transfer/promotion/appointment will promote representivity will receive preference. It is the Department\u2019s intention to promote equity through the filling of all numeric targets as contained in the Employment Equity Plan. To facilitate this process successfully, an indication of race, gender and disability status is required. It is the applicant\u2019s responsibility to have foreign qualifications evaluated by the South African Qualifications Authority (SAQA). The Department reserves the right not to appoint. Disabled people are encouraged to apply. If you do not receive any response from us within 3 months, please accept your application was unsuccessful. Enquiries Mr. Albert Mthembu Tel: 060 983 2677 Number of Posts 1 Closing Date 2020/07/24 Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
